## Configuration Details

### Correct Implementation Pattern
The project follows the recommended pattern for Next.js 13.5+ with App Router:
1. ✅ Uses `@vercel/speed-insights/next` import (not `/react`)
2. ✅ Component added to root layout (`app/layout.tsx`)
3. ✅ Placed inside `<body>` tag after children
4. ✅ No additional configuration needed (auto-detects routes)

### Why This Works
- Next.js App Router automatically provides routing context
- The `SpeedInsights` component from `/next` doesn't require manual route prop
- Placement after children ensures proper page load tracking
- Works seamlessly with other Vercel services (Analytics also installed)

## Conclusion

**No code changes were required.** The Vercel Speed Insights package was already installed and correctly configured according to best practices for Next.js 16 with App Router. The implementation is production-ready and will automatically track page load performance when deployed to Vercel.

